This project uses the AI-Integrated Development (AID) methodology.

## Knowledge Base
- Read `.aid/knowledge/INDEX.md` for a map of all project documentation
- Always consult relevant KB documents before making changes
- The KB is the single source of truth for architecture, conventions, and patterns

## Workspace Structure (per FR2 area-STATE rule)

AID has three areas; each has exactly one STATE.md (absorbing what used to be
per-skill / per-artifact state files).

```
.aid/
  knowledge/                ← Discovery area (persistent KB)
    INDEX.md                ← map of all KB docs
    README.md               ← completeness table + revision history
    STATE.md                ← Discovery area state (was DISCOVERY-STATE.md + SUMMARY-STATE.md)
    {14 KB documents}       ← architecture, coding-standards, schemas, pipeline-contracts, ...
  work-NNN-{name}/          ← Work area (per work — one full dev lifecycle)
    STATE.md                ← Work area state (was INTERVIEW-STATE.md + per-feature/per-task state)
    REQUIREMENTS.md
    PLAN.md
    features/
      feature-NNN-{name}/
        SPEC.md             ← requirements + technical specification
    tasks/
      task-NNN-{name}.md    ← per-task acceptance criteria
  {monitor area STATE deferred per FR2 OQ-3 — per-work, future}
```

## Workflow
- Every change should be traceable to a task or requirement
- Follow the current phase (Init → Discover → Interview → Specify → Plan → Detail → Implement → Review → Test → Deploy → Track → Triage)
- Produce verifiable artifacts at each phase
- Quality gates must pass before proceeding
